Japan Seeks Most Milling Wheat in Seven Weeks in Tender

-- B y   A y a   T a k a d a
-- 
2011-06-14T08:32:44Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-06-14/japan-seeks-most-milling-wheat-in-seven-weeks-in-tender-1-.html
Japan  is seeking to buy 259,303
metric tons of milling wheat from the U.S.,  Canada  and  Australia 
in a regular tender on June 16, the Ministry of Agriculture,
Forestry and Fisheries said.  The volume sought is the largest since April 28, when the
government bought 336,518 tons. Shipment is set from Aug. 1 to
Aug. 31, Masafumi Otsuka at the ministry’s grain-trade division
said today by phone.  The ministry, which controls overseas purchases and
domestic sales of wheat to stabilize supply, is  Asia ’s largest
buyer as a single entity. It has bought 1.12 million tons
through regular tenders this fiscal year, compared with 5.16
million tons purchased in the year ended March 31.  Details of this week’s tender are listed below:  To contact the reporter on this story:
